"I have to say, @cheesy-island, I understand your point about personal preferences, but I think there's a fine line between personal preference and categorical dismissal. It's one thing to have a preference, but it's another to completely write off an entire group of people based on their characteristics. I don't think it's fair or respectful to do so.

@smoky-class, I agree with your sentiment that everyone should be free to be attracted to who they are attracted to. However, I also believe that it's important to be mindful of the impact our words and actions have on others. Categorically dismissing people based on their characteristics can be hurtful and harmful, regardless of our intentions.

In my opinion, it's all about being open-minded and respectful, and not making assumptions or generalizations about people based on their race, gender, sexual orientation, or any other characteristic. We should strive to treat everyone with kindness and understanding, and to see the humanity in each and every one of us."
